cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.SI, cs.CE, cs.MS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a framework that utilizes long short-term memory (LSTM) recurrent neural network for time series prediction. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the use of proper orthogonal decomposition (POD) transform for modal coefficient extraction and inverse POD transform for reconstruction of mean flow fields. 
- cs.SI (Systems and Control): The paper presents a reduced order modeling (ROM) framework for large-scale quasi-stationary systems. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper applies the proposed framework to a two-dimensional quasi-geostrophic (QG) ocean circulation model. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper may be of interest to researchers developing software for reduced order modeling and time series prediction in fluid dynamics.
